# GitHub Repository And Account

For this project, always use the main repository and the `diegograsso` GitHub account.

- The only intended remote is `origin` pointing to `https://github.com/martinmateo1/supply-chain-ethglobal.git`.
- Do not use or recreate a `fork` remote for `agrodiego/supply-chain-ethglobal` unless the user explicitly asks.
- Before pushing, creating PRs, or using `gh`, verify the active GitHub user with `gh api user --jq '.login'`; it must return `diegograsso`.
- If plain Git operations need credentials, prefer this repo-local helper over global config changes:

```sh
git config --local credential.https://github.com.helper "!gh auth git-credential"
```

- If the remote drifts, restore it with:

```sh
git remote set-url origin https://github.com/martinmateo1/supply-chain-ethglobal.git
```
